quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
7,74,"And call to mind when He made you successors after 'Ad and gave you power in the earth so that you took for yourselves palaces in its plains and hewed out dwellings in the mountains. {1} Remember, then, the wondrous bounties of Allah and do not go about creating mischief in the land.' {2}",footnotes:1:The Thamud were highly skilful in rock-carving
7,75,"The haughty elders of his people said to those believers who had been oppressed: 'Do you know that Salih is one sent forth with a message from his Lord?' They, replied: 'Surely we believe in the message with which he has been sent.'"
7,76,"The haughty ones remarked. 'Most certainly we disbelieve in that which you believe.'"
7,77,"Then they hamstrung the she-camel, {1} disdainfuliy disobeyed the commandment of their Lord, and said: '0 Salih! Bring upon us the scourge with which you threatened us if you are truly a Messenger [of Allah].'",footnotes:1:Although the she-camel was killed by an individual
7,78,"Thereupon a shocking catastrophe seized them, {1} so that they lay prostrate in their dwellings.",footnotes:1:Other Qur'anic expressions used for the calamity are 'rajifah' (earthquake) (al-Nazi'at 79: 6); 'sayah' (awesome cry)(Hud 11: 67); 'Sa'iqah' (thunderbolt) (al-Baqarah 2: 55); and 'taghiyah'' (roaring noise) (al-Haqqah 69: 5).
7,79,"And Salih left them, saying: 'O my people! I conveyed to you the message of my Lord and gave you good advice; but you have no liking for your well-wishers.'"
7,80,"And remember when We sent Lot [as a Messeng to his people and he said to them: {1} 'Do you realize you practise an indecency of which no other people in the world were guilty of before you?",footnotes:1:The land inhabited by the people of Lot
7,81,"You approach men lustfully in place of women. You are a people who exceed all bounds.' {1}",footnotes:1:The Qur'an refers elsewhere to the many evil deeds of the people of Lot. Here the Qur'an confines itself to mentioning that most ignominious of crimes which invited God's scourge upon them. The hideous act of sodomy
